under’ (the fish)."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Bostock was born in 1419, in Davenham, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Richard Bulkeley in 1442, in Alverstoke, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1485, in Cheadle, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1419–1485":"1419–1485","1417–1500":"1417–1500","1443–1485":"1443–1485","1443–1490":"1443–1490","1500":"1500","1443":"1443","1442":"1442","1485":"1485","1419":"1419","1490":"1490","1417":"1417","Alverstoke, Hampshire, England":"Alverstoke, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Holcroft Hall, Lancashire, England":"Holcroft Hall, Lancashire, England","Cheadle, Cheshire, England":"Cheadle, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Davenham, Cheshire, England":"Davenham, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1419–1485":"1419–1485","1417–1500":"1417–1500","1443–1485":"1443–1485","1443–1490":"1443–1490","1500":"1500","1443":"1443","1442":"1442","1485":"1485","1419":"1419","1490":"1490","1417":"1417","Alverstoke, Hampshire, England":"Alverstoke, Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Holcro